        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 4:59PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 458 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fernley, or 7 miles northwest of Lahontan Reservoir, moving northeast
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fernley, Hazen, Fernley Sink Near I-80, and Fernley - Tiger Field
Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
